tinues wiping until he gathers the wipe in his hand and lifts it from the cleaned surface.\n\nThe focus moves to a bathroom or sink area with white tile and a chrome faucet. A white Lysol No-Touch hand soap dispenser sits beside the sink, topped with a teal-coloured soap refill. A hand is held under the dispenser’s spout as soap is dispensed without touching the unit. Fine-print text at the bottom mentions CDC guidelines about washing hands and notes that Lysol No-Touch Hand Soap does not kill viruses.\n\nThen the man is shown at the sink with two young children. A young girl with long brown hair sits or stands on the left, smiling and rubbing her hands together. A young boy with short brown hair, wearing a red-and-blue plaid shirt, stands in the middle, also smiling with his hands raised near the soap dispenser. The man leans in from the right, smiling warmly at them. The white no-touch dispenser is visible in the foreground near the sink. On-screen text at the bottom compares the product “against bacteria” with a leading antibacterial hand soap.\n\nThe woman returns with the blue-and-white Lysol Disinfectant Spray near a white door and a silver lever-style door handle. She holds the can close to the handle and sprays toward it; a fine mist is visible around the metal surface. Text at the bottom again states that Lysol Disinfectant Spray helps stop the spread of germs on hard, non-porous surfaces when used as directed. She then stands by a sunlit glass door or tall window, holding the can at her side. Outside, greenery and soft daylight are visible, and inside there is a small side table with framed family photos and a lamp.\n\nThe setting changes to a backyard covered with fallen leaves in warm afternoon light. The man, now in a light blue hoodie and jeans, plays with the children. A brown football arcs through the air toward him. The boy runs in from the background wearing a green hoodie over his plaid shirt, while the girl, in a red cardigan, watches from the side. The man crouches and catches the football against his chest. The boy rushes up behind him, and they tumble playfully onto the grass. The man lands on his side still holding the football, the boy climbs over him laughing, and the girl kneels beside them, reaching toward the ball and the man’s shoulder. A bright blue ribbon-like graphic sweeps across the grass and curls around the family, forming a protective-looking loop as they lie together and play.\n\nThe commercial ends on a clean product display against a softly lit home background. From left to right are a yellow Lysol Disinfecting Wipes canister, a blue-and-white Lysol Disinfectant Spray can, and a white Lysol No-Touch hand soap dispenser with its teal refill attached. A blue ribbon graphic curves beside the products. The Lysol logo is prominent on all three items. On-screen text includes “lysol.com” near the bottom right, with a small “Discover rb.com” mark near the upper right.",
